What is a cloud trail ?
  :- A CloudTrail is a service provided by Amazon Web Services (AWS) that enables governance, compliance, operational auditing, and risk auditing of your AWS 
     account. It records API calls made on your AWS account and stores the information in log files in Amazon S3 or CloudWatch Logs.

Why do we use trails, what is the exact purpose of enabling the trail in cloud production accounts ?
   :- Purpose of CloudTrail:  The main purpose of enabling CloudTrail in a production AWS account is to gain visibility into the actions being taken within 
      the account. This includes tracking who is making API calls, what actions they are performing, and when these actions are taking place. This information 
      is crucial for security, compliance, and operational analysis. 

Explain how we can create a trail in aws cloud trail?
    :-  To create a trail in AWS CloudTrail, you can follow these steps:
         Log in to the AWS Management Console.
         Navigate to the CloudTrail service.
        Click on "Trails" in the  menu.
        Click on "Create trail" and follow the prompts to configure your trail, including specifying the S3 bucket where you want the logs to be stored and 
        any other settings you require.

How can we enable logging for S3 bucket using cloud trails ?
     :-When we create a trail in CloudTrail, we can specify the S3 bucket where you want the logs to be stored. By selecting the appropriate bucket, 
      CloudTrail will automatically start logging events related to that bucket.

How do you get the list of all created trailers in your production account ?
     :-You can view a list of all created trails in your AWS account by navigating to the CloudTrail service and selecting "Trails" from the  menu.

Can we create a trail for a multi region, if yes then how can we configure it ?
    :-Yes, you can create a trail that logs events from multiple AWS regions. When creating the trail, you can select the option to apply it to all regions, 
      or you can specify individual regions that you want to include

How can we disable the logging for certain events, services in cloud trail, If yes so explain how ?
    :-You can configure event selectors to filter out specific events or services that you do not want to log. By defining these filters in your trail 
      settings, you can exclude certain types of events from being recorded.

Real time use case of cloud trail ?
    :-A real-time use case of CloudTrail is monitoring for security incidents or compliance violations. By continuously analyzing the CloudTrail logs, 
      organizations can detect unauthorized access attempts, unusual behavior, or non-compliant actions in near real-time.

What is cloud trail event history ?
    :-CloudTrail Event History provides a record of all API activity within your AWS account over the past 90 days. This allows you to search and analyze 
      past events, even if you didn't have a trail configured at the time

What is log file integrity validation in cloud trail ?
    :-Log file integrity validation in CloudTrail ensures that the log files have not been tampered with or modified. CloudTrail accomplishes this by 
      generating a cryptographic hash for each log file and storing it alongside the log file. You can use this hash to verify the integrity of the log 
      files.
